@startuml IdempotentDesign

title High-Level Design: Idempotent API / Service

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam ArrowColor #555555
skinparam ActorBorderColor #333333
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
skinparam NoteBorderColor #F9A825

' ─────────────────────────────────────────
'  Actors / External Systems
' ─────────────────────────────────────────
actor "Client" as client

' ─────────────────────────────────────────
'  Components
' ─────────────────────────────────────────
package "API Gateway / Load Balancer" {
    component [API Gateway] as gateway
}

package "Application Service" {
    component [Idempotency Filter\n/ Middleware] as filter
    component [Business Logic\nService] as service
}

package "Idempotency Store" {
    database "Idempotency Key\nCache / DB\n(Redis / DB Table)" as keyStore
}

package "Downstream Systems" {
    component [Payment / Order\nProcessor] as downstream
    database "Primary Database" as primaryDB
}

' ─────────────────────────────────────────
'  Relationships
' ─────────────────────────────────────────
client          --> gateway    : HTTP Request\n+ Idempotency-Key header
gateway         --> filter     : Forward request
filter          --> keyStore   : 1. Lookup Idempotency Key
keyStore        --> filter     : Key found? (DUPLICATE / NEW)

filter          --> client     : [DUPLICATE] Return cached response\n(HTTP 200 / stored result)

filter          --> service    : [NEW] Proceed with processing
service         --> downstream : Execute business operation
downstream      --> primaryDB  : Persist state
downstream      --> service    : Operation result
service         --> keyStore   : 2. Store key + response\n(with TTL)
service         --> client     : Return fresh response

' ─────────────────────────────────────────
'  Notes
' ─────────────────────────────────────────
note right of filter
  **Idempotency Key Rules:**
  - Generated by client (UUID v4)
  - Sent via header: Idempotency-Key
  - Unique per logical operation
  - TTL: e.g. 24 hours
end note

note right of keyStore
  **Key Entry Schema:**
  {
    idempotency_key : string (PK)
    request_hash    : string
    response_body   : JSON
    status_code     : int
    created_at      : timestamp
    expires_at      : timestamp
  }
end note

note bottom of downstream
  **Idempotent Operations:**
  - PUT  (naturally idempotent)
  - DELETE (naturally idempotent)
  - POST (requires key-based guard)
end note

' ─────────────────────────────────────────
'  Sequence of states
' ─────────────────────────────────────────
legend right
  | Color / Arrow | Meaning |
  | --> (solid)   | Request / Response flow |
  | [DUPLICATE]   | Key already processed – return cached |
  | [NEW]         | First-time request – execute normally |
endlegend

@enduml

